fields.description:
h3.Summary

When a site has both Confluence and Jira, users can benefit from the [integration between Jira and Confluence|https://support.atlassian.com/jira-service-management-cloud/docs/integrate-jira-cloud-with-confluence/] so gadgets could be used to display Jira information in pages.

When the site has only Jira and Confluence (not Jira Service Management included), if a user does not have product access for Jira, upon viewing the gadgets and their configuration, the following message will be displayed:

{code}
{"message":"ASAP token from issues 'micros-group/confluence' requested subject impersonation as 'aaid:<AAID here>', but no corresponding user account could be found","status-code":403} 
{code}

h3.Suggestion

Although the 403 matches with a forbidden message, having a message that states that the user must have Jira permissions to view or edit the gadget would help administrators understanding the next course of action.

This is a suggestion to improve the message to state that the user must have Jira product access to be able to view and edit the gadgets.
